The paper deals with matching problems in geometric graphs, which are graphs whose vertices are points in the plane and whose edges are straight-line segments. This falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses algorithms for computing such matchings, which falls under data structures (cs.DS). The study of geometric graphs and their properties falls under graph theory (cs.GR) and the paper deals with various types of matchings, which falls under combinatorics (cs.CC).
